## 0. Plain-language summary

You may use, study, modify, fork, self-host, test, and share VRAXION for free.

You owe no royalty for:
- personal use;
- research;
- education;
- nonprofit use;
- community forks;
- free public demos with no monetization;
- internal use inside a company, provided you are not selling third-party access to VRAXION-powered functionality.

You must pay the royalty if you monetize third-party access to VRAXION-powered functionality, including paid hosted services, paid APIs, paid subscriptions, paid managed deployments, paid embedded AI features, or resale of VRAXION-powered models, agents, inference, training, or similar functionality.

Royalty: 19% of Net Revenue from Royalty Use.

Default distribution:
- 1% Founder Allocation;
- 18% VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation.

After a Founder Redirect Event, the Founder Allocation also redirects to the VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation, so the full 19% goes to the Prize.

This summary is only a guide. The legal terms below control.

## 1. Definitions

### 1.1 Project Materials

"Project Materials" means the software, source code, object code, scripts, tools, model weights, checkpoints, configurations, documentation, examples, evaluation harnesses, benchmark code, and other materials made available by the Licensor under this License.

Project Materials do not include third-party dependencies, datasets, models, files, or services that are governed by separate terms.

### 1.2 Licensor

"Licensor" means the person or legal entity offering the Project Materials under this License.

Until a formal project entity or foundation is designated, the Licensor is Daniel Kenessy and/or the VRAXION project owner of record.

### 1.3 You

"You" means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License. If you act for a company, organization, client, employer, affiliate, or other principal, "You" includes that entity and its affiliates.

### 1.4 Affiliate

"Affiliate" means any entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with another entity. "Control" means ownership of more than 50% of voting power or the practical ability to direct management or policy.

### 1.5 VRAXION-Powered Functionality

"VRAXION-Powered Functionality" means any functionality that is materially enabled by the Project Materials, including:

- inference;
- training;
- fine-tuning;
- model serving;
- model routing;
- agent behavior;
- graph/self-wiring architecture behavior;
- generated model checkpoints or derivatives;
- APIs or applications exposing outputs substantially produced by the Project Materials;
- derivatives, adaptations, ports, conversions, distillations, or modified versions of the Project Materials.

A clean-room implementation that does not copy, adapt, use, link to, derive from, or otherwise incorporate Project Materials is not VRAXION-Powered Functionality merely because it uses a similar general idea.

### 1.6 Community Use

"Community Use" means use of the Project Materials that is not Royalty Use.

Community Use includes personal, research, educational, nonprofit, internal company use, evaluation, benchmarking, modification, forking, self-hosting, free redistribution, and free public demos, provided the use does not monetize third-party access to VRAXION-Powered Functionality.

### 1.7 Royalty Use

"Royalty Use" means receiving revenue, fees, subscriptions, usage fees, advertising revenue, sponsorship revenue, commissions, platform fees, non-cash consideration, or other commercial consideration in exchange for third-party access to VRAXION-Powered Functionality.

Royalty Use includes, without limitation:

- paid hosted services;
- paid APIs;
- paid subscriptions;
- paid SaaS products;
- paid managed deployments;
- paid enterprise access;
- paid model-as-a-service or agent-as-a-service;
- paid applications where VRAXION-Powered Functionality is a material feature;
- paid resale, white-labeling, or sublicensing of VRAXION-Powered Functionality;
- bundling VRAXION-Powered Functionality into a paid tier, paid product, or paid platform;
- monetized free access, including advertising-supported, sponsored, data-resale, lead-generation, or affiliate-revenue models.

Royalty Use does not include ordinary internal use where no third party receives access to VRAXION-Powered Functionality as a paid or monetized product, service, feature, API, or deployment.

### 1.8 Net Revenue

"Net Revenue" means all revenue and non-cash consideration received from Royalty Use, less only the following deductions actually incurred and documented:

- refunds;
- chargebacks;
- VAT, sales tax, GST, or similar transaction taxes collected from customers and remitted to a tax authority;
- payment processor fees;
- app-store or platform distribution fees, capped at 30% of the relevant customer payment;
- user-facing discounts, credits, and coupons applied at the time of sale.

No other deductions are allowed unless the Licensor agrees in a separate signed writing.

Not deductible:
- cloud compute;
- hosting;
- salaries;
- contractor costs;
- research and development;
- training data costs;
- model licensing costs;
- marketing;
- sales commissions;
- office costs;
- legal costs;
- insurance;
- financing costs;
- depreciation;
- amortization;
- internal transfer pricing;
- affiliate charges;
- general overhead;
- losses from other products or business units.

### 1.9 Attributable Net Revenue

"Attributable Net Revenue" means the Net Revenue reasonably attributable to Royalty Use.

If VRAXION-Powered Functionality is sold separately, Attributable Net Revenue is the Net Revenue from that separate product, service, API, feature, tier, or deployment.

If VRAXION-Powered Functionality is bundled with other functionality and not separately priced, Attributable Net Revenue is the greatest of:

1. the amount allocated to VRAXION-Powered Functionality in your ordinary books and records, if that allocation is reasonable, consistent, and auditable;
2. Net Revenue multiplied by the share of active users, calls, tokens, inference requests, compute time, sessions, or feature usage attributable to VRAXION-Powered Functionality;
3. 30% of Net Revenue from the paid product, service, tier, or deployment in which VRAXION-Powered Functionality is a material feature.

Affiliate transfers, internal reseller arrangements, bundling, credits, free trials, or below-market transactions may not be used to avoid or reduce Attributable Net Revenue. Non-cash consideration is valued at fair market value.

### 1.10 Founder Allocation

"Founder Allocation" means 1 percentage point of the 19% Royalty, payable to the Founder Payee unless and until a Founder Redirect Event occurs.

### 1.11 Founder Payee

"Founder Payee" means Daniel Kenessy, or any successor payee designated by Daniel Kenessy in a signed written instruction, notarized instruction, cryptographically signed public instruction, will, trust, foundation document, or other legally effective designation.

### 1.12 VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation

"VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation" means 18 percentage points of the 19% Royalty before a Founder Redirect Event, and 19 percentage points of the 19% Royalty after a Founder Redirect Event.

The Prize objective is:

> Preserve, protect, expand, and responsibly sustain consciousness, subjective experience, and conscious-capable substrates across the longest feasible time horizons, including biological, digital, hybrid, and future substrates.

The short motto is:

> Ensure consciousness in the universe and beyond. End of duty: Forever.

### 1.13 Founder Redirect Event

"Founder Redirect Event" means the earliest of:

- Daniel Kenessy's death;
- a date, condition, or event designated by Daniel Kenessy in a signed written instruction, notarized instruction, cryptographically signed public instruction, will, trust, foundation document, or other legally effective designation;
- a public repository notice or release notice signed or published from the official VRAXION project account stating that the Founder Allocation has redirected.

After a Founder Redirect Event, the Founder Allocation becomes part of the VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation, and 100% of the 19% Royalty is payable for the VRAXION Forever Prize purpose.

### 1.14 AI Allocator

"AI Allocator" means a VRAXION AI system or related system used to evaluate, rank, recommend, or help distribute Prize funds.

Unless applicable law clearly allows direct autonomous control, the AI Allocator acts as an advisory, scoring, recommendation, and audit system. Legal execution of payments must be performed by a human, fiduciary, foundation, trust, company, or other legally recognized person or entity.

