## 3. Royalty Use license grant

Subject to this License, the Licensor grants You a worldwide, non-exclusive, non-transferable license to make Royalty Use of the Project Materials only if You comply with all Royalty Use requirements in this section.

### 3.1 Royalty

For Royalty Use, You must pay 19% of Attributable Net Revenue.

Before a Founder Redirect Event, the 19% Royalty is allocated as follows:

- 1% of Attributable Net Revenue to the Founder Allocation;
- 18% of Attributable Net Revenue to the VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation.

After a Founder Redirect Event, the full 19% of Attributable Net Revenue is allocated to the VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation.

The total royalty is always 19%, not 20%.

### 3.2 Registration

You must notify the Licensor in writing within 30 days after first Royalty Use.

The notice must include:

- your legal name;
- billing contact;
- product or service name;
- description of the VRAXION-Powered Functionality;
- start date of Royalty Use;
- reporting contact;
- payment contact.

### 3.3 Reporting

You must provide a royalty report within 45 days after the end of each calendar quarter in which You make Royalty Use.

Each report must state:

- gross receipts from Royalty Use;
- deductions used to calculate Net Revenue;
- Attributable Net Revenue;
- royalty due;
- allocation between Founder Allocation and VRAXION Forever Prize Allocation;
- methodology used for bundled products or mixed services;
- number of active users, calls, tokens, requests, sessions, or other usage metrics reasonably needed to audit attribution.

### 3.4 Payment

Royalty payments are due within 45 days after the end of each calendar quarter.

Payments must be made in EUR unless the Licensor agrees otherwise in writing.

If payment details for one allocation are not available, You must pay the available allocation on time and hold the unavailable allocation in segregated escrow or reserve until the Licensor provides valid payment instructions.

### 3.5 Audit

You must keep complete and accurate records relating to Royalty Use for at least 5 years.

No more than once per calendar year, the Licensor may appoint an independent accountant or auditor to audit those records on reasonable notice and under reasonable confidentiality terms.

If an audit finds an underpayment of more than 5% for any audited period, You must promptly pay the underpayment, reasonable audit costs, and interest at 1% per month or the maximum allowed by law, whichever is lower.

### 3.6 No avoidance

You may not avoid, reduce, or disguise Royalty Use by:

- routing revenue through affiliates;
- bundling VRAXION-Powered Functionality without reasonable attribution;
- calling fees "support", "compute", "platform", "membership", "donation", "credit", or another label while providing monetized access;
- giving away VRAXION-Powered Functionality while monetizing it through ads, sponsorship, data resale, affiliate fees, lead generation, or similar consideration;
- selling through an affiliate, reseller, partner, marketplace, or white-label arrangement at below-market transfer prices;
- using credits, coupons, or free trials that are funded by third-party commercial consideration.

